se toLet Others View,00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:05.270Tejas can open a script,run it, and play it,00:01:05.270 --> 00:01:07.250but he cannot change it.00:01:07.250 --> 00:01:08.540We can let othersview our script00:01:08.540 --> 00:01:11.770by copying the web addresslisted in a dialog box.00:01:11.770 --> 00:01:13.280Anyone who opensthat address link00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.730will then be ableto view our script.00:01:15.730 --> 00:01:18.370If we want to share the scriptonly with specific people,00:01:18.370 --> 00:01:20.330like a teacher or a classmate,00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:23.590we can also typein their EarSketch usernames.00:01:23.590 --> 00:01:27.070In this case,we will use Tejas’ user ID.00:01:27.070 --> 00:01:28.980He will now receivea notification in EarSketch00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:31.180inviting him to open our script.00:01:31.180 --> 00:01:33.380In the dialog, we can also type00:01:33.380 --> 00:01:36.140in the descriptionof our script.00:01:36.140 --> 00:01:38.545When we are done,click on the blue Save button00:01:38.545 --> 00:01:41.290on the bottom-rightof the dialogue.00:01:43.620 --> 00:01:45.530If you choose Let Others Edit,00:01:45.530 --> 00:01:47.160other EarSketch userscan both view00:01:47.160 --> 00:01:50.860and edit our scriptjust like in Google Docs.00:01:50.860 --> 00:01:52.120This lets uscollaborate with other00:01:52.120 --> 00:01:55.180EarSketch users to write scripttogether at the same time.00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:56.450OK. Let’s invite00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:59.170Tejas to collaboratewith us on a script.00:01:59.170 --> 00:02:01.600Type his EarSketch usernameinto his dialog box00:02:01.600 --> 00:02:04.250and click the blueSave button on the bottom-right.00:02:04.250 --> 00:02:06.400He will then receivea notification in EarSketch00:02:06.400 --> 00:02:09.010inviting him to openand edit our script.00:02:09.010 --> 00:02:11.850If more than one user is editingthe script at the same time,00:02:11.850 --> 00:02:13.070we’ll each see00:02:13.070 --> 00:02:17.340what the other usersare typing in the code editor.00:02:17.340 --> 00:02:19.340No matter what career paththat you choose in your life,00:02:19.340 --> 00:02:21.320collaborationwill be very important.00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.270EarSketch’s sharingand collaboration features00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:25.830will prepare you for that.Thanks for watching!00:02:25.830 --> 00:02:30.730[monophonic electronic tones]